owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._decorator: Decorating logic contract producing a creature's metadata, and picture.

params._expirationBlocks: Number of blocks after Witnet randomness is generated,  during which creatures may be minted.
params._signator: Externally-owned account authorize to sign egg's info before minting.

startHatching().details: During the hatching period the tender will remain in 'Hatching status'. Once thehatching period expires, tender status will automatically change to 'Freezed'.

stopBatching().details: While request is being attended, tender will remain in 'Randomizing' status.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

setParameters(address,uint8[],uint256).notice: Change batch parameters. Only possible while in 'Batching' status.

startHatching().notice: Starts hatching, which means that minting of creatures will start to be possible, until the hatching period expires (see `_state.expirationBlocks`).

stopBatching().notice: Stops batching, which means: (a) parameters cannot change anymore, and (b) a  random number will requested to the Witnet Decentralized Oracle Network.
